{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-2155","published":"2024-09-20T11:09:10Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:20:14.629483Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-31585"],"summary":"ffmpeg security update","details":"FFmpeg is a complete and free Internet live audio and video broadcasting solution for Linux/Unix. It also includes a digital VCR. It can encode in real time in many formats including MPEG1 audio and video, MPEG4, h263, ac3, asf, avi, real, mjpeg, and flash.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nFFmpeg version n5.1 to n6.1 was discovered to contain an Off-by-one Error vulnerability in libavfilter/avf_showspectrum.c. This vulnerability allows attackers to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) via a crafted input.(CVE-2024-31585)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"ffmpeg","ecosystem":"openEuler:22.03-LTS-SP3","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/ffmpeg&distro=openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP3"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["ffmpeg-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-debuginfo-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-debugsource-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-devel-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-libs-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","libavdevice-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm"],"src":["ffmpeg-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["ffmpeg-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-debuginfo-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-debugsource-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-devel-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-libs-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.x86_64.rpm","libavdevice-4.2.4-17.oe2203sp3.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2024-2155.json"}}],"references":[{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://www.openeuler.org/zh/security/security-bulletins/detail/?id=openEuler-SA-2024-2155"},{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-31585"}],"database_specific":{"severity":"Medium"}}